{"cursor":"34222","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Oral Rehydration Therapy' ('ORT') is a simple treatment for dehydration\nassociated with diarrhea, particularly gastroenteritis or gastroenteropathy,\nsuch as that caused by cholera or rotavirus. ORT consists of a solution of salts\nand sugars that is taken by mouth. It is used around the world, most\nsignificantly in the developing world, where it saves millions of children a\nyear from death due to diarrhea, the second leading cause of death (after\npneumonia) in children under five.\n","linknr":844,"url":"Oral_rehydration_solution","recorded":1362902668,"links":70,"instances":["chemistry","anatomy","unit","unit"],"pdf":["http://www.unicef.org/sowc08/docs/sowc08.pdf","http://www.unicef.org/sowc08/docs/sowc08.pdf","http://amimc.org.mx/congresos/medicina_viajero/Tratamiento_rehidratacion.pdf","http://amimc.org.mx/congresos/medicina_viajero/Tratamiento_rehidratacion.pdf","http://cid.oxfordjournals.org/content/37/3/398.full.pdf","http://cid.oxfordjournals.org/content/37/3/398.full.pdf","http://www.unicef.org/publications/files/1946-2006_Sixty_Years_for_Children.pdf","http://www.unicef.org/publications/files/1946-2006_Sixty_Years_for_Children.pdf","http://www.princemahidolaward.org/publications/PMA_Program06.pdf","http://www.princemahidolaward.org/publications/PMA_Program06.pdf","http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2005/9241593180.pdf","http://www.who.int/topics/test/food_safety/safe_food_travel.pdf","http://www.who.int/entity/bulletin/archives/78(10)1246.pdf","http://www.who.int/entity/bulletin/archives/78(10)1246.pdf","http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD002847/pdf","http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD002847/pdf","http://www.supply.unicef.dk/catalogue/NewORSQ&A.pdf","http://www.supply.unicef.dk/catalogue/NewORSQ&A.pdf","http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2005/9241593180.pdf","http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2005/9241593180.pdf","http://libdoc.